name: Bulbasaur
description: It carries a seed on its back right from birth. As it grows older, the seed also grows larger.

name: Ivysaur
description: If the bud on its back starts to smell sweet, it is evidence that the large flower will soon bloom.

name: Venusaur
description: It is able to convert sunlight into energy. As a result, it is more powerful in the summertime.

name: Charmander
description: The flame on its tail indicates CHARMANDER’s life force. If it is healthy, the flame burns brightly.

name: Charmeleon
description: It has a barbaric nature. In battle, it whips its fiery tail around and slashes away with sharp claws.

name: Charizard
description: Breathing intense, hot flames, it can melt almost anything. Its breath inflicts terrible pain on enemies.

name: Squirtle
description: The shell, which hardens soon after it is born, is resilient. If you poke it, it will bounce back out.

name: Wartortle
description: It cleverly controls its furry ears and tail to maintain its balance while swimming.

name: Blastoise
description: The rocket cannons on its shell fire jets of water capable of punching holes through thick steel.

name: Caterpie
description: Its feet have suction cups designed to stick to any surface. It tenaciously climbs trees to forage.

name: Metapod
description: It prepares for evolution by hardening its shell as much as possible to protect its soft body.

name: Butterfree
description: Water-repellent powder on its wings enables it to collect honey, even in the heaviest of rains.

name: Weedle
description: It attacks using a two-inch poison barb on its head. It can usually be found under the leaves it eats.

name: Kakuna
description: From this form, it will grow into an adult. As its body becomes softer, the external shell hardens.

name: Beedrill
description: It has three poison barbs. The barb on its tail secretes the most powerful poison.

name: Pidgey
description: Common in grassy areas and forests, it is very docile and will chase off enemies by flapping up sand.

name: Pidgeotto
description: It renders its prey immobile using  well-developed claws, then carries the prey more than 60 miles to its nest.

name: Pidgeot
description: It spreads its beautiful wings wide to frighten its enemies. It can fly at Mach 2 speed.

name: Rattata
description: Living wherever there is food available, it ceaselessly scavenges for edibles the entire day.

name: Raticate
description: Its whiskers help it to maintain balance. Its fangs never stop growing, so it gnaws to pare them down.

name: Spearow
description: Very protective of its territory, it flaps its short wings busily to dart around at high speed.

name: Fearow
description: It cleverly uses its thin, long beak to pluck and eat small insects that hide under the ground.

name: Ekans
description: It always hides in grass. When first born, it has no poison, so its bite is painful, but harmless.

name: Arbok
description: With a very vengeful nature, it won’t give up the chase, no matter how far, once it targets its prey.

name: Pikachu
description: It raises its tail to check its surroundings. The tail is sometimes struck by lightning in this pose.

name: Raichu
description: If the electric pouches in its cheeks become fully charged, both ears will stand straight up.

name: Sandshrew
description: Disliking water, it lives in deep burrows in arid areas. It can roll itself instantly into a ball.

name: Sandslash
description: If it digs at an incredible pace, it may snap off its spikes and claws. They grow back in a day.

name: Nidoran-f
description: Although not very combative, it will torment its foes with poison spikes if it is threatened in any way.

name: Nidorina
description: It has a calm and caring nature. Because its horn grows slowly, it prefers not to fight.

name: Nidoqueen
description: It uses its scaly, rugged body to seal the entrance of its nest and protect its young from predators.

name: Nidoran-m
description: It raises its big ears to check its surroundings. It will strike first if it senses any danger.

name: Nidorino
description: Quick to anger, it stabs enemies with its horn to inject a powerful poison when it becomes agitated.

name: Nidoking
description: Its tail is thick and powerful. If it binds an enemy, it can render the victim helpless quite easily.

name: Clefairy
description: Its adorable behavior and cry make it highly popular. However, this cute Pokémon is rarely found.

name: Clefable
description: Its very sensitive ears let it distinguish distant sounds. As a result, it prefers quiet places.

name: Vulpix
description: If it is attacked by an enemy that is stronger than itself, it feigns injury to fool the enemy and escapes.

name: Ninetales
description: Its nine beautiful tails are filled with a wondrous energy that could keep it alive for 1,000 years.

name: Jigglypuff
description: Looking into its cute, round eyes causes it to sing a relaxing melody, inducing its enemies to sleep.

name: Wigglytuff
description: It has a very fine fur. Take care not to make it angry, or it may inflate steadily and hit with a body slam.

name: Zubat
description: Capable of flying safely in dark places, it emits ultrasonic cries to check for any obstacles.

name: Golbat
description: It can drink more than 10 ounces of blood at once. If it has too much, it gets heavy and flies clumsily.

name: Oddish
description: If exposed to moonlight, it starts to move. It roams far and wide at night to scatter its seeds.

name: Gloom
description: It secretes a sticky, drool-like honey. Although sweet, it smells too repulsive to get very close.

name: Vileplume
description: The bud bursts into bloom with a bang. It then starts scattering allergenic, poisonous pollen.

name: Paras
description: As its body grows, large mushrooms named tochukaso start sprouting out of its back.

name: Parasect
description: The larger the mushroom on its back grows, the stronger the mushroom spores it scatters.

name: Venonat
description: Poison oozes from all over its body. It catches and eats small bugs at night that are attracted by light.

name: Venomoth
description: The powder on its wings is poisonous if it is dark in hue. If it is light in hue, it causes paralysis.

name: Diglett
description: If a DIGLETT digs through a field, it leaves the soil perfectly tilled and ideal for planting crops.

name: Dugtrio
description: Extremely powerful, they can dig through even the hardest ground to a depth of over 60 miles.

name: Meowth
description: It loves anything that shines. It especially adores coins that it picks up and secretly hoards.

name: Persian
description: Its lithe muscles allow it to walk without making a sound. It attacks in an instant.

name: Psyduck
description: If its chronic headache peaks, it may exhibit odd powers. It seems unable to recall such an episode.

name: Golduck
description: It appears by waterways at dusk. It may use telekinetic powers if its forehead glows mysteriously.

name: Mankey
description: It’s unsafe to approach if it gets violently enraged for no reason and can’t distinguish friends from foes.

name: Primeape
description: It becomes wildly furious if it even senses someone looking at it. It chases anyone that meets its glare.

name: Growlithe
description: Extremely loyal, it will fearlessly bark at any opponent to protect its own Trainer from harm.

name: Arcanine
description: Its magnificent bark conveys a sense of majesty. Anyone hearing it can’t help but grovel before it.

name: Poliwag
description: The direction of its belly spiral differs by area. The equator is thought to have an effect on this.

name: Poliwhirl
description: The skin on most of its body is moist. However, the skin on its belly spiral feels smooth.

name: Poliwrath
description: Although an energetic, skilled swimmer that uses all of its muscles, it lives on dry land.

name: Abra
description: If it decides to teleport randomly, it evokes the illusion that it has created copies of itself.

name: Kadabra
description: If it uses its abilities, it emits special alpha waves that cause machines to malfunction.

name: Alakazam
description: Its brain cells multiply continually until it dies. As a result, it remembers everything.

name: Machop
description: It loves to work out and build its muscles. It is never satisfied, even if it trains hard all day long.

name: Machoke
description: The muscles covering its body teem with power. Even when still, it exudes an amazing sense of strength.

name: Machamp
description: It uses its four powerful arms to pin the limbs of its foe, then throws the victim over the horizon.

name: Bellsprout
description: It plants its feet deep underground to replenish water. It can’t escape its enemy while it’s rooted.

name: Weepinbell
description: If its prey is bigger than its mouth, it slices up the victim with sharp leaves, then eats every morsel.

name: Victreebel
description: This horrifying plant Pokémon attracts prey with aromatic honey, then melts them in its mouth.

name: Tentacool
description: It drifts aimlessly in waves. Very difficult to see in water, it may not be noticed until it stings.

name: Tentacruel
description: In battle, it extends all 80 of its tentacles to entrap its opponent inside a poisonous net.

name: Geodude
description: It uses its arms to steadily climb steep mountain paths. It swings its fists around if angered.

name: Graveler
description: A slow walker, it rolls to move. It pays no attention to any object that happens to be in its path.

name: Golem
description: It is capable of blowing itself up. It uses this explosive force to jump from mountain to mountain.

name: Ponyta
description: Its hind legs, which have hooves that are harder than diamond, kick back at any presence it senses behind it.

name: Rapidash
description: With incredible acceleration, it reaches its top speed of 150 mph after running just 10 steps.

name: Slowpoke
description: A sweet sap leaks from its tail’s tip. Although not nutritious, the tail is pleasant to chew on.

name: Slowbro
description: Naturally dull to begin with, it lost its ability to feel pain due to SHELLDER’s seeping poison.

name: Magnemite
description: The units at the sides of its body generate antigravity energy to keep it aloft in the air.

name: Magneton
description: The MAGNEMITE are united by a magnetism so powerful, it dries all moisture in its vicinity.

name: Farfetchd
description: If it eats the plant stalk it carries as emergency rations, it runs off in search of a new stalk.

name: Doduo
description: It races through grassy plains with powerful strides, leaving footprints up to four inches deep.

name: Dodrio
description: If one of the heads gets to eat, the others will be satisfied, too, and they will stop squabbling.

name: Seel
description: In daytime, it is often found asleep on the seabed in shallow waters. Its nostrils close while it swims.

name: Dewgong
description: It loves frigid seas with ice floes. It uses its long tail to change swimming direction quickly.

name: Grimer
description: Wherever GRIMER has passed, so many germs are left behind that no plants will ever grow again.

name: Muk
description: Its body is made of a powerful poison. Touching it accidentally will cause a fever that requires bed rest.

name: Shellder
description: Grains of sand trapped in its shells mix with its body fluids to form beautiful pearls.

name: Cloyster
description: CLOYSTER that live in seas with harsh tidal currents grow large, sharp spikes on their shells.

name: Gastly
description: Its body is made of gas. Despite lacking substance, it can envelop an opponent of any size and cause suffocation.

name: Haunter
description: Its tongue is made of gas. If licked, its victim starts shaking constantly until death eventually comes.

name: Gengar
description: To steal the life of its target, it slips into the prey’s shadow and silently waits for an opportunity.

name: Onix
description: It rapidly bores through the ground at 50 mph by squirming and twisting its massive, rugged body.

name: Drowzee
description: It remembers every dream it eats. It rarely eats the dreams of adults because children’s are much tastier.

name: Hypno
description: Always holding a pendulum that it swings at a steady rhythm, it causes drowsiness in anyone nearby.

name: Krabby
description: The pincers break off easily. If it loses a pincer, it somehow becomes incapable of walking sideways.

name: Kingler
description: Its pincers grow peculiarly large. If it lifts the pincers too fast, it loses its balance and staggers.

name: Voltorb
description: It was discovered when Poké Balls were introduced. It is said that there is some connection.

name: Electrode
description: It stores an overflowing amount of electric energy inside its body. Even a small shock makes it explode.

name: Exeggcute
description: Using telepathy only they can employ, they always form a cluster of six EXEGGCUTE.

name: Exeggutor
description: If a head drops off, it emits a telepathic call in search of others to form an EXEGGCUTE cluster.

name: Cubone
description: It always wears the skull of its dead mother, so no one has any idea what its hidden face looks like.

name: Marowak
description: It collects bones from an unknown place. Some whisper that a MAROWAK graveyard exists somewhere in the world.

name: Hitmonlee
description: If it starts kicking repeatedly, both legs will stretch even longer to strike a fleeing foe.

name: Hitmonchan
description: Its punches slice the air. They are launched at such high speed, even a slight graze could cause a burn.

name: Lickitung
description: Its long tongue, slathered with a gooey saliva, sticks to anything, so it is very useful.

name: Koffing
description: The poisonous gases it contains are a little bit lighter than air, keeping it slightly airborne.

name: Weezing
description: Top-grade perfume is made using its internal poison gases by diluting them to the highest level.

name: Rhyhorn
description: It doesn’t care if there is anything in its way. It just charges and destroys all obstacles.

name: Rhydon
description: Its brain developed when it began walking on hind legs. Its thick hide protects it even in magma.

name: Chansey
description: Being few in number and difficult to capture, it is said to bring happiness to the Trainer who catches it.

name: Tangela
description: It tangles any moving thing with its vines. Their subtle shaking is ticklish if you get ensnared.

name: Kangaskhan
description: To protect its young, it will never give up during battle, no matter how badly wounded it is.

name: Horsea
description: Its big, developed fins move rapidly, allowing it to swim backward while still facing forward.

name: Seadra
description: Its fin-tips leak poison. Its fins and bones are highly valued as ingredients in herbal medicine.

name: Goldeen
description: A strong swimmer, it is capable of swimming nonstop up fast streams at a steady speed of five knots per hour.

name: Seaking
description: Using its horn, it bores holes in riverbed boulders, making nests to prevent its eggs from washing away.

name: Staryu
description: Even if its body is torn, it can regenerate as long as the glowing central core remains intact.

name: Starmie
description: Regardless of the environment it lives in, its body grows to form a symmetrical geometric shape.

name: Mr-mime
description: Its fingertips emit a peculiar force field that hardens air to create an actual wall.

name: Scyther
description: When it moves, it leaves only a blur. If it hides in grass, its protective coloration makes it invisible.

name: Jynx
description: It speaks a language similar to that of humans. However, it seems to use dancing to communicate.

name: Electabuzz
description: Its body constantly discharges electricity. Getting close to it will make your hair stand on end.

name: Magmar
description: The fiery surface of its body gives off a wavering, rippling glare that is similar to the sun.

name: Pinsir
description: It swings its long pincer horns wildly to attack. During cold periods, it hides deep in forests.

name: Tauros
description: After heightening its will to fight by whipping itself with its three tails, it charges at full speed.

name: Magikarp
description: For no reason, it jumps and splashes about, making it easy for predators like PIDGEOTTO to catch it mid-jump.

name: Gyarados
description: Once it appears, it goes on a rampage. It remains enraged until it demolishes everything around it.

name: Lapras
description: It ferries people across the sea on its back. It may sing an enchanting cry if it is in a good mood.

name: Ditto
description: Its transformation ability is perfect. However, if made to laugh, it can’t maintain its disguise.

name: Eevee
description: Its irregularly configured DNA is affected by its surroundings. It evolves if its environment changes.

name: Vaporeon
description: It prefers beautiful shores. With cells similar to water molecules, it could melt in water.

name: Jolteon
description: Every hair on its body starts to stand sharply on end if it becomes charged with electricity.

name: Flareon
description: It fluffs out its fur collar to cool down its body temperature, which can reach 1,650 degrees Fahrenheit.

name: Porygon
description: A manmade Pokémon that came about as a result of research. It is programmed with only basic motions.

name: Omanyte
description: This Pokémon from ancient times is said to have navigated the sea by adeptly twisting its 10 tentacles.

name: Omastar
description: Once wrapped around its prey, it never lets go. It eats the prey by tearing at it with sharp fangs.

name: Kabuto
description: This Pokémon lived in ancient times. On rare occasions, it has been discovered as a living fossil.

name: Kabutops
description: With sharp claws, this ferocious, ancient Pokémon rips apart prey and sucks their body fluids.

name: Aerodactyl
description: This vicious Pokémon is said to have flown in ancient skies while shrieking high-pitched cries.

name: Snorlax
description: Its stomach’s digestive juices can dissolve any kind of poison. It can even eat things off the ground.

name: Articuno
description: One of the legendary bird Pokémon, it chills moisture in the atmosphere to create snow while flying.

name: Zapdos
description: This legendary bird Pokémon is said to appear only when a thundercloud parts into two halves.

name: Moltres
description: This legendary bird Pokémon is said to bring early spring to the wintry lands it visits.

name: Dratini
description: This Pokémon is full of life energy. It continually sheds its skin and grows steadily larger.

name: Dragonair
description: Its crystalline orbs appear to give this Pokémon the power to freely control the weather.

name: Dragonite
description: This marine Pokémon has an impressive build that lets it freely fly over raging seas without trouble.

name: Mewtwo
description: It usually remains motionless to conserve energy, so that it may unleash its full power in battle.

name: Mew
description: Its DNA is said to contain the genetic codes of all Pokémon, so it can use all kinds of techniques.

name: Chikorita
description: Its pleasantly aromatic leaf has the ability to check humidity and temperature.

name: Bayleef
description: A spicy aroma emanates from around its neck. The aroma acts as a stimulant to restore health.

name: Meganium
description: MEGANIUM’s breath has the power to revive dead grass and plants. It can make them healthy again.

name: Cyndaquil
description: It usually stays hunched over. If it is angry or surprised, it shoots flames out of its back.

name: Quilava
description: This Pokémon is fully covered by nonflammable fur. It can withstand any kind of fire attack.

name: Typhlosion
description: It has a secret, devastating move. It rubs its blazing fur together to cause huge explosions.

name: Totodile
description: It is small but rough and tough. It won’t hesitate to take a bite out of anything that moves.

name: Croconaw
description: It opens its huge jaws wide when attacking. If it loses any fangs while biting, they grow back in.

name: Feraligatr
description: It is hard for it to support its weight out of water, so it sometimes gets down on all fours. But it moves fast.

name: Sentret
description: It stands on its tail so it can see a long way. If it spots an enemy, it cries loudly to warn its kind.

name: Furret
description: There is no telling where the tail begins. Despite its short legs, it is quick and likes to chase RATTATA.

name: Hoothoot
description: It has a perfect sense of time. Whatever happens, it keeps rhythm by precisely tilting its head in time.

name: Noctowl
description: When it needs to think, it rotates its head 180 degrees to sharpen its intellectual power.

name: Ledyba
description: When the weather turns cold, lots of LEDYBA gather from everywhere to cluster and keep each other warm.

name: Ledian
description: The spot patterns on its back grow larger or smaller depending on the number of stars in the night sky.

name: Spinarak
description: It spins a web using fine--but durable--thread. It then waits patiently for prey to be trapped.

name: Ariados
description: A single strand of a special string is endlessly spun out of its rear. The string leads back to its nest.

name: Crobat
description: The development of wings on its legs enables it to fly fast but also makes it tough to stop and rest.

name: Chinchou
description: On the dark ocean floor, its only means of communication is its constantly flashing lights.

name: Lanturn
description: It blinds prey with an intense burst of light. With the prey incapacitated, the Pokémon swallows it in a single gulp.

name: Pichu
description: Despite its small size, it can zap even adult humans. However, if it does so, it also surprises itself.

name: Cleffa
description: When numerous meteors illuminate the night sky, sightings of CLEFFA strangely increase.

name: Igglybuff
description: Its extremely flexible and elastic body makes it bounce continuously--anytime, anywhere.

name: Togepi
description: A proverb claims that happiness will come to anyone who can make a sleeping TOGEPI stand up.

name: Togetic
description: It grows dispirited if it is not with kind people. It can float in midair without moving its wings.

name: Natu
description: It usually forages for food on the ground but may, on rare occasions, hop onto branches to peck at shoots.

name: Xatu
description: In South America, it is said that its right eye sees the future and its left eye views the past.

name: Mareep
description: Its fleece grows continually. In the summer, the fleece is fully shed, but it grows back in a week.

name: Flaaffy
description: Its fluffy fleece easily stores electricity. Its rubbery hide keeps it from being electrocuted.

name: Ampharos
description: The bright light on its tail can be seen far away. It has been treasured since ancient times as a beacon.

name: Bellossom
description: Plentiful in the tropics. When it dances, its petals rub together and make a pleasant ringing sound.

name: Marill
description: The end of its tail serves as a buoy that keeps it from drowning, even in a vicious current.

name: Azumarill
description: When it plays in water, it rolls up its elongated ears to prevent their insides from getting wet.

name: Sudowoodo
description: It disguises itself as a tree to avoid attack. It hates water, so it will disappear if it starts raining.

name: Politoed
description: Whenever three or more of these get together, they sing in a loud voice that sounds like bellowing.

name: Hoppip
description: Its body is so light, it must grip the ground firmly with its feet to keep from being blown away.

name: Skiploom
description: It spreads its petals to absorb sunlight. It also floats in the air to get closer to the sun.

name: Jumpluff
description: Drifts on seasonal winds and spreads its cotton-like spores all over the world to make more offspring.

name: Aipom
description: It lives atop tall trees. When leaping from branch to branch, it deftly uses its tail for balance.

name: Sunkern
description: It lives by drinking only dewdrops from under the leaves of plants. It is said that it eats nothing else.

name: Sunflora
description: In the daytime, it rushes about in a hectic manner, but it comes to a complete stop when the sun sets.

name: Yanma
description: Its large eyes can scan 360 degrees. It looks in all directions to seek out insects as its prey.

name: Wooper
description: When it walks around on the ground, it coats its body with a slimy, poisonous film.

name: Quagsire
description: Due to its relaxed and carefree attitude, it often bumps its head on boulders and boat hulls as it swims.

name: Espeon
description: By reading air currents, it can predict things such as the weather or its foe’s next move.

name: Umbreon
description: When darkness falls, the rings on the body begin to glow, striking fear in the hearts of anyone nearby.

name: Murkrow
description: It is said that when chased, it lures its attacker onto dark mountain trails where the foe will get lost.

name: Slowking
description: When its head was bitten, toxins entered SLOWPOKE’s head and unlocked an extraordinary power.

name: Misdreavus
description: It loves to bite and yank people’s hair from behind without warning, just to see their shocked reactions.

name: Unown
description: Its flat, thin body is always stuck on walls. Its shape appears to have some meaning.

name: Wobbuffet
description: To keep its pitch-black tail hidden, it lives quietly in the darkness. It is never first to attack.

name: Girafarig
description: Its tail, which also contains a small brain, may bite on its own if it notices an alluring smell.

name: Pineco
description: It hangs and waits for flying insect prey to come near. It does not move about much on its own.

name: Forretress
description: It remains immovably rooted to its tree. It scatters pieces of its hard shell to drive its enemies away.

name: Dunsparce
description: If spotted, it escapes by burrowing with its tail. It can float just slightly using its wings.

name: Gligar
description: It usually clings to cliffs. When it spots its prey, it spreads its wings and glides down to attack.

name: Steelix
description: It’s said that if an ONIX lives for 100 years, its composition becomes diamondlike as it evolves into a STEELIX.

name: Snubbull
description: It has an active, playful nature. Many women like to frolic with it because of its affectionate ways.

name: Granbull
description: Because its fangs are too heavy, it always keeps its head tilted down. However, its bite is powerful.

name: Qwilfish
description: The small spikes covering its body developed from scales. They inject a toxin that causes fainting.

name: Scizor
description: Its wings are not used for flying. They are flapped at high speed to adjust its body temperature.

name: Shuckle
description: It stores berries inside its shell. To avoid attacks, it hides beneath rocks and remains completely still.

name: Heracross
description: It is usually docile, but if it is disturbed while sipping honey, it chases off the intruder with its horn.

name: Sneasel
description: Vicious in nature, it drives PIDGEY from their nests and scavenges any leftovers it can find.

name: Teddiursa
description: Before food becomes scarce in wintertime, its habit is to hoard food in many hidden locations.

name: Ursaring
description: With its ability to distinguish any aroma, it unfailingly finds all food buried deep underground.

name: Slugma
description: A common sight in volcanic areas, it slowly slithers around in a constant search for warm places.

name: Magcargo
description: Its brittle shell occasionally spouts intense flames that  circulate throughout its body.

name: Swinub
description: If it smells something enticing, it dashes off headlong to find the source of the aroma.

name: Piloswine
description: If it charges at an enemy, the hairs on its back stand up straight. It is very sensitive to sound.

name: Corsola
description: In a south-sea nation, the people live in communities that are built on groups of these Pokémon.

name: Remoraid
description: Using its dorsal fin as a suction pad, it clings to a MANTINE’s underside to scavenge for leftovers.

name: Octillery
description: It instinctively sneaks into rocky holes. If it gets sleepy, it steals the nest of a fellow OCTILLERY.

name: Delibird
description: It nests at the edge of sharp cliffs. It spends all day carrying food to its awaiting chicks.

name: Mantine
description: Swimming freely in open seas, it may fly out of the water and over the waves if it builds up enough speed.

name: Skarmory
description: After nesting in bramble bushes, the wings of its chicks grow hard from scratches by thorns.

name: Houndour
description: To corner prey, they check each other’s location using barks that only they can understand.

name: Houndoom
description: Upon hearing its eerie howls, other Pokémon get the shivers and head straight back to their nests.

name: Kingdra
description: It sleeps deep on the ocean floor to build its energy. It is said to cause tornadoes as it wakes.

name: Phanpy
description: As a sign of affection, it bumps with its snout. However, it is so strong, it may send you flying.

name: Donphan
description: The longer and bigger its tusks, the higher its rank in its herd. The tusks take long to grow.

name: Porygon2
description: Further research enhanced its  abilities. Sometimes, it may exhibit motions that were not programmed.

name: Stantler
description: Those who stare at its antlers will gradually lose control of their senses and be unable to stand.

name: Smeargle
description: Once it becomes an adult, it has a tendency to let its comrades plant footprints on its back.

name: Tyrogue
description: Even though it is small, it can’t be ignored because it will slug any handy target without warning.

name: Hitmontop
description: It launches kicks while spinning. If it spins at high speed, it may bore its way into the ground.

name: Smoochum
description: It always rocks its head slowly backwards and forwards as if it is trying to kiss someone.

name: Elekid
description: Even in the most vicious storm, this Pokémon plays happily if thunder rumbles in the sky.

name: Magby
description: It is found in volcanic craters. Its body temperature is over 1,100 degrees Fahrenheit, so don’t underestimate it.

name: Miltank
description: If it is around babies, the milk it produces contains much more nutrition than usual.

name: Blissey
description: It has a very compassionate nature. If it sees a sick Pokémon, it will nurse the sufferer back to health.

name: Raikou
description: A Pokémon that races across the land while barking a cry that sounds like crashing thunder.

name: Entei
description: A Pokémon that races across the land. It is said that one is born every time a new volcano appears.

name: Suicune
description: This Pokémon races across the land. It is said that north winds will somehow blow whenever it appears.

name: Larvitar
description: It is born deep underground. It can’t emerge until it has entirely consumed the soil around it.

name: Pupitar
description: Even sealed in its shell, it can move freely. Hard and fast, it has outstanding destructive power.

name: Tyranitar
description: Extremely strong, it can change the landscape. It has an insolent nature that makes it not care about others.

name: Lugia
description: It is said to be the guardian of the seas. It is rumored to have been seen on the night of a storm.

name: Ho-oh
description: A legend says that its body glows in seven colors. A rainbow is said to form behind it when it flies.

name: Celebi
description: When CELEBI disappears deep in a forest, it is said to leave behind an egg it brought from the future.

name: Treecko
description: Small hooks on the bottom of its feet catch on walls and ceilings. That is how it can hang from above.

name: Grovyle
description: It leaps from tree branch to tree branch quite swiftly. It shows astounding agility.

name: Sceptile
description: It agilely leaps about the jungle and uses the sharp leaves on its arms to strike its prey.

name: Torchic
description: Inside its body is a place where it keeps a small flame. Hug it! It will be as warm as a hot-water bottle.

name: Combusken
description: During a battle, the hot flame in its body increases. Its kicks have outstanding destructive power.

name: Blaziken
description: It can clear a 30-story building in a leap. Its fiery punches scorch its foes.

name: Mudkip
description: Its power can crush boulders. It rests by covering itself with mud at the bottom of a river.

name: Marshtomp
description: Living on muddy ground that provides poor footing has made its legs sturdy.

name: Swampert
description: Its arms are hard as rock. With one swing, it can break a boulder into pieces.

name: Poochyena
description: It chases its prey until the victim becomes exhausted. However, it turns tail if the prey strikes back.

name: Mightyena
description: It chases down prey in a pack of around ten. They defeat foes with perfectly coordinated teamwork.

name: Zigzagoon
description: It gets interested in everything, which is why it zigs and zags. It is good at finding items.

name: Linoone
description: When running in a straight line, it can easily top 60 miles an hour. It has a tough time with curved roads.

name: Wurmple
description: It lives among the tall grass and in forests. It repels attacks by  raising up the spikes on its rear.

name: Silcoon
description: Having wrapped silk around the branches of a tree, it quiescently awaits evolution.

name: Beautifly
description: Vibrantly patterned wings are its prominent feature. It sucks sweet flower nectar with its long mouth.

name: Cascoon
description: It endures attacks with patience, because the more pain before evolution, the sturdier it becomes.

name: Dustox
description: It scatters its fine dust all over when it is attacked. It is a nocturnal Pokémon.

name: Lotad
description: Its leaf grew too large for it to live on land. That is how it began to live floating in the water.

name: Lombre
description: It is nocturnal and becomes active at nightfall. It feeds on aquatic mosses that grow in the riverbed.

name: Ludicolo
description: If it hears festive music, it begins moving in rhythm in order to amplify its power.

name: Seedot
description: It attaches itself to a tree branch using the top of its head. Strong winds can sometimes make it fall.

name: Nuzleaf
description: It lives deep in forests. With the leaf on its head, it makes a flute whose song makes listeners uneasy.

name: Shiftry
description: It lives quietly in the deep forest. It is said to create chilly winter winds with the fans it holds.

name: Taillow
description: When it gets cold, they migrate, flying over 180 miles a day. It hunts for tasty prey.

name: Swellow
description: It dives at a steep angle as soon as it spots its prey. It catches its prey with sharp claws.

name: Wingull
description: It soars on updrafts without flapping its wings. It makes a nest on sheer cliffs at the sea’s edge.

name: Pelipper
description: It protects its young in its beak. It bobs on waves, resting on them on days when the waters are calm.

name: Ralts
description: The horns on its head provide a strong power that enables it to sense people’s emotions.

name: Kirlia
description: It has a psychic power that enables it to distort the space around it and see into the future.

name: Gardevoir
description: It unleashes psychokinetic energy at full power when protecting a Trainer it has bonded closely with.

name: Surskit
description: It secretes a thick, sweet-scented syrup from the tip of its head. It lives on weed-choked ponds.

name: Masquerain
description: It flaps its four wings to hover and fly freely in any direction-- to and fro and sideways.

name: Shroomish
description: If it senses danger, it scatters spores from the top of its head to protect itself.

name: Breloom
description: It scatters poisonous spores and throws powerful punches while its foe is hampered by inhaled spores.

name: Slakoth
description: The way SLAKOTH lolls around makes anyone who watches it feel like doing the same.

name: Vigoroth
description: Its stress level rises if it cannot keep moving constantly. Too much stress makes it feel sick.

name: Slaking
description: The world’s laziest Pokémon. It moves to another spot when there’s no food left within its reach.

name: Nincada
description: It can sometimes live underground for more than 10 years. It absorbs nutrients from the roots of trees.

name: Ninjask
description: Its cry leaves a lasting headache if heard for too long. It moves so quickly that it is almost invisible.

name: Shedinja
description: A strange Pokémon--it flies without moving its wings, has a hollow shell for a body, and does not breathe.

name: Whismur
description: If it senses danger, it scares the foe by crying out with the volume of a jet-plane engine.

name: Loudred
description: It shouts loudly by inhaling air, and then uses its well-developed stomach muscles to exhale.

name: Exploud
description: Its roar in battle shakes the ground like a tremor--or like an earthquake has struck.

name: Makuhita
description: It toughens up by slamming into thick trees over and over. It gains a sturdy body and dauntless spirit.

name: Hariyama
description: It loves challenging others to tests of strength. It has the power to stop a train with a slap.

name: Azurill
description: Its tail is packed full of the nutrients it needs to grow.

name: Nosepass
description: If two of these meet, they cannot get too close because their noses repel each other.

name: Skitty
description: It’s adorable when it chases its own tail. It’s difficult to earn its trust.

name: Delcatty
description: It dislikes dirty places. It often searches for a comfortable place in which to groom itself.

name: Sableye
description: It dwells in the darkness of caves. It uses its sharp claws to dig up gems to nourish itself.

name: Mawile
description: It chomps with its gaping mouth. Its huge jaws are actually steel horns that have been transformed.

name: Aron
description: When it evolves, it sheds the steel carapace that covered its whole body and develops a new one.

name: Lairon
description: It loves iron ore. Groups of them fight for territory by bashing one another with their steel bodies.

name: Aggron
description: You can tell its age by the length of its iron horns. It claims an entire mountain as its territory.

name: Meditite
description: It meditates to heighten its inner energy and to float in the air. It eats one berry a day.

name: Medicham
description: Through yoga training, it gained the psychic power to predict its foe’s next move.

name: Electrike
description: It stores electricity in its fur. It gives off sparks from all over its body in seasons when the air is dry.

name: Manectric
description: Its nest can be found where a thunderbolt hits. It is discharging electricity from its mane.

name: Plusle
description: It absorbs electricity from telephone poles. It shorts out its body to create crackling noises.

name: Minun
description: Exposure to electricity from MINUN and PLUSLE promotes blood circulation and relaxes muscles.

name: Volbeat
description: It emits light from its tail to communicate. It loves the sweet aroma given off by ILLUMISE.

name: Illumise
description: Its fragrance attracts a swarm of VOLBEAT, so they draw over 200 patterns in the night sky.

name: Roselia
description: ROSELIA that drink nutritionally rich springwater are said to reveal rare coloration when they bloom.

name: Gulpin
description: It has a small heart and brain. Its stomach comprises most of its body, with enzymes to dissolve anything.

name: Swalot
description: It gulps anything that fits in its mouth. Its special enzymes can dissolve anything.

name: Carvanha
description: They form packs to attack boats and rip out their hulls to sink them. They live in rivers in the jungle.

name: Sharpedo
description: It can swim at speeds of 75 mph by jetting seawater through its body. It is the bandit of the sea.

name: Wailmer
description: It bounces playfully like a ball. The more seawater it swallows, the higher it bounces.

name: Wailord
description: It is the largest of all identified Pokémon. They jump as a pack to herd their prey.

name: Numel
description: The flaming magma it stores in the hump on its back is the source of its tremendous power.

name: Camerupt
description: It lives in the crater of a volcano. It is well known that the humps on its back erupt every 10 years.

name: Torkoal
description: You find abandoned coal mines full of them. They dig tirelessly in search of coal.

name: Spoink
description: It bounces around on its tail to keep its heart pumping. It carries a pearl from CLAMPERL on its head.

name: Grumpig
description: It can perform odd dance steps to influence foes. Its style of dancing became hugely popular overseas.

name: Spinda
description: The chances of two SPINDA having identical spot patterns is less than one in four billion.

name: Trapinch
description: Its nest is a sloped, bowl-like pit in the desert. Once something has fallen in, there is no escape.

name: Vibrava
description: It vibrates its wings vigorously, creating ultrasonic waves that cause serious headaches.

name: Flygon
description: It is nicknamed “The Desert Spirit” because the flapping of its wings sounds like a woman singing.

name: Cacnea
description: It lives in arid locations. Its yellow flowers bloom once a year.

name: Cacturne
description: Packs of them follow travelers through the desert until the travelers can no longer move.

name: Swablu
description: Its wings bring cottony clouds to mind. It grooms with springwater and loves to sit on heads.

name: Altaria
description: It flies gracefully through the sky. Its melodic humming makes you feel like you’re in a dream.

name: Zangoose
description: Its fur would all stand on end if it smelled a SEVIPER nearby. Its sharp claws tear up its foes.

name: Seviper
description: In battle, it uses its bladed tail to counter any ZANGOOSE. It secretes a deadly venom in its tail.

name: Lunatone
description: It was discovered at the site of a meteor strike 40 years ago. Its stare can lull its foes to sleep.

name: Solrock
description: When it rotates itself, it gives off light similar to the sun, thus blinding its foes.

name: Barboach
description: BARBOACH uses its whiskers to taste things just as a person uses his or her tongue to taste things.

name: Whiscash
description: It claims a large swamp to itself. If a foe comes near it, it sets off tremors by thrashing around.

name: Corphish
description: It was originally a Pokémon from afar that escaped to the wild. It can adapt to the dirtiest river.

name: Crawdaunt
description: A brutish Pokémon that loves to battle. It will crash itself into any foe that approaches its nest.

name: Baltoy
description: It moves while spinning around on its single foot. Some BALTOY have been seen spinning on their heads.

name: Claydol
description: It is said that it originates from clay dolls made by an ancient civilization.

name: Lileep
description: It disguises its tentacles as flowers to attract and catch prey. It became extinct in ancient times.

name: Cradily
description: It lives in warm seas. Its heavy body weighs it down so it won’t get washed away in rough weather.

name: Anorith
description: An ancestral Pokémon that lived in the ocean. Over time, its eight feet transformed into wings.

name: Armaldo
description: Its enormous, retractable claws can cut through most anything. Its entire body is clad in sturdy plates.

name: Feebas
description: It is the shabbiest Pokémon of all. It forms in schools and lives at the bottom of rivers.

name: Milotic
description: It’s said that a glimpse of a MILOTIC and its beauty will calm any hostile emotions you’re feeling.

name: Castform
description: This Pokémon can change its cells, taking different forms based on the temperature and humidity.

name: Kecleon
description: It changes its shading to match its surroundings so it can sneak up on prey. Only its belly patterns stay fixed.

name: Shuppet
description: It uses its horn to feed on envy and malice, or so it’s said. It’s very active at night.

name: Banette
description: This Pokémon developed from an abandoned doll that amassed a grudge. It is seen in dark alleys.

name: Duskull
description: If it finds bad children who won’t listen to their parents, it will spirit them away--or so it’s said.

name: Dusclops
description: Anyone who dares peer into its body to see its spectral ball of fire will have their spirit stolen away.

name: Tropius
description: The bunch of fruit around its neck ripens twice a year and is delicious. It’s a highly favored tropical snack.

name: Chimecho
description: It uses the sucker on its head to hang from a tree or from eaves. It can produce seven different tones.

name: Absol
description: It has the ability to foretell natural disasters. Its life span is over a hundred years.

name: Wynaut
description: It tends to move in a pack. Individuals squash against one another to toughen their spirits.

name: Snorunt
description: It’s said that if they are seen at midnight, they’ll cause heavy snow. They eat snow and ice to survive.

name: Glalie
description: It can instantly freeze moisture in the atmosphere. It uses this power to freeze its foes.

name: Spheal
description: It crosses the oceans by rolling itself on drifting ice. Fluffy fur keeps it warm when the temperature is below freezing.

name: Sealeo
description: It has a very sensitive nose. It touches new things with its nose to examine them.

name: Walrein
description: It shatters drift ice with its strong tusks. Its thick layer of blubber repels enemy attacks.

name: Clamperl
description: When it evolves, it makes a mysterious pearl that amplifies psychic powers when it’s held.

name: Huntail
description: It lives deep in the pitch-dark sea. It attracts prey by moving its tail in mimicry of a small animal.

name: Gorebyss
description: Its pink body becomes more vivid with the rise of water temperatures in the springtime.

name: Relicanth
description: Discovered by chance during deep-sea explorations, it has not changed since ancient times.

name: Luvdisc
description: Its heart-shaped body makes it popular. In some places, you would give a LUVDISC to someone you love.

name: Bagon
description: Its well-developed neck muscles and ironlike head can smash boulders into pieces.

name: Shelgon
description: It surrounds its body in an iron-hard shell to accumulate enough power to evolve.

name: Salamence
description: It’s uncontrollable if enraged. It flies around spouting flames and scorching fields and mountains.

name: Beldum
description: The magnetic force generated by its body repels the ground’s natural magnetism, letting it float.

name: Metang
description: When two BELDUM fuse together, a magnetic nervous system places their brains in union.

name: Metagross
description: It folds its four legs when flying. Its four brains are said to be superior to a supercomputer.

name: Regirock
description: The same rocks that form its body have been found in ground layers around the world.

name: Regice
description: It is said to have slept in a glacier for thousands of years. Its body can’t be melted, even by magma.

name: Registeel
description: Its body is said to be harder than any kind of metal. A study has revealed that its body is hollow.

name: Latias
description: It communicates using telepathy. Its body is covered in down that refracts light to make it invisible.

name: Latios
description: It understands human speech and is highly intelligent. It is a tender Pokémon that dislikes fighting.

name: Kyogre
description: A mythical Pokémon said to have swelled the seas with rain and tidal waves. It battled with GROUDON.

name: Groudon
description: Said to have expanded the lands by evaporating water with raging heat. It battled titanically with KYOGRE.

name: Rayquaza
description: It flies in the ozone layer, way up high in the sky. Until recently, no one had ever seen it.

name: Jirachi
description: Generations have believed that any wish written on a note on its head will come true when it awakens.

name: Deoxys
description: DNA from a space virus mutated and became a Pokémon. It appears where auroras are seen.

name: Turtwig
description: Photosynthesis occurs across its body under the sun. The shell on its back is actually hardened soil.

name: Grotle
description: A GROTLE that lives in the forest is said to have its own secret springwater.

name: Torterra
description: Ancient people imagined that beneath the ground, a gigantic TORTERRA dwelled.

name: Chimchar
description: The gas made in its belly burns from its rear end. The fire burns weakly when it feels sick.

name: Monferno
description: A bigger fire on its tail and a brighter blue pattern on its face means its rank in its pack is higher.

name: Infernape
description: It tosses its enemies around with agility. It uses all its limbs to fight in its own unique style.

name: Piplup
description: It doesn’t like to be taken care of. It’s difficult to bond with since it won’t listen to its Trainer.

name: Prinplup
description: It lives a solitary life. Its wings deliver wicked blows that can snap even the thickest of trees.

name: Empoleon
description: It avoids unnecessary disputes, but it will decimate anything that threatens its pride.

name: Starly
description: They flock around mountains and fields, chasing after bug Pokémon. Their singing is noisy and annoying.

name: Staravia
description: They maintain huge flocks, although fierce scuffles break out between various flocks.

name: Staraptor
description: When STARAVIA evolve into STARAPTOR, they leave the flock to live alone. They have sturdy wings.

name: Bidoof
description: It lives in groups by the water.  It chews up boulders and trees around its nest with its incisors.

name: Bibarel
description: It busily makes its nest with stacks of branches and roots it has cut up with its sharp incisors.

name: Kricketot
description: When its antennae hit each other, it sounds like the music of a xylophone.

name: Kricketune
description: By allowing its cry to resonate in the hollow of its belly, it produces a captivating sound.

name: Shinx
description: The extension and contraction of its muscles generates electricity. Its fur glows when it’s in trouble.

name: Luxio
description: By gathering their tails together, they collectively generate powerful electricity from their claws.

name: Luxray
description: LUXRAY’s ability to see through objects comes in handy when it’s scouting for danger.

name: Budew
description: When it feels the sun’s warm touch, it opens its bud to release pollen. It lives alongside clear pools.

name: Roserade
description: Its sweet aroma attracts prey. Then it spews poison. The more toxic it is, the sweeter its aroma.

name: Cranidos
description: CRANIDOS toughen up their already rock-hard heads by headbutting one another.

name: Rampardos
description: Its skull withstands impacts of any magnitude. As a result, its brain never gets the chance to grow.

name: Shieldon
description: It was generated from a fossil dug out of a layer of clay that was older than anyone knows. It has a sturdy face.

name: Bastiodon
description: When attacked, they form a wall. Their rock-hard faces serve to protect them from the attacks.

name: Burmy
description: It covers itself with a cloak to shelter from the cold. When it’s hot, its cloak is thinner.

name: Wormadam
description: It is said that a WORMADAM that evolves on a cold day will have a thicker cloak.

name: Mothim
description: It flutters around at night and steals honey from the COMBEE hive.

name: Combee
description: At night, COMBEE sleep in a group of about a thousand, packed closely together in a lump.

name: Vespiquen
description: It raises grubs in the holes in its body. It secretes pheromones to control COMBEE.

name: Pachirisu
description: It’s one of the kinds of Pokémon  with electric cheek pouches. It shoots charges from its tail.

name: Buizel
description: It inflates its flotation sac, keeping its face above water in order to watch for prey movement.

name: Floatzel
description: With its flotation sac inflated, it can carry people on its back. It deflates the sac before it dives.

name: Cherubi
description: It evolves by sucking the energy out of the small ball where it had been storing nutrients.

name: Cherrim
description: During times of strong sunlight, its bud blooms, its petals open fully, and it becomes very active.

name: Shellos
description: Its shape and coloration vary, depending on its habitat.

name: Gastrodon
description: When its natural enemy attacks, it oozes purple fluid and escapes.

name: Ambipom
description: It is very difficult to dodge the consecutive strikes of its two tails.

name: Drifloon
description: It is whispered that any child who mistakes DRIFLOON for a balloon and holds on to it could wind up missing.

name: Drifblim
description: It can generate and release gas within its body. That’s how it can control the altitude of its drift.

name: Buneary
description: You can tell how it feels by the way it rolls its ears. When it’s scared, both ears are rolled up.

name: Lopunny
description: It sheds its fur twice a year. Its winter fur is soft and fluffy.

name: Mismagius
description: Its cries sound like incantations to torment the foe. It appears where you least expect it.

name: Honchkrow
description: It is merciless by nature. It is said that it never forgives the mistakes of its MURKROW followers.

name: Glameow
description: When it’s happy, GLAMEOW demonstrates beautiful movements of its tail, like a dancing ribbon.

name: Purugly
description: It would claim another Pokémon’s nest as its own if it finds a nest sufficiently comfortable.

name: Chingling
description: It emits high-frequency cries that  people can’t hear. Once it starts, it can cry for an awfully long time.

name: Stunky
description: The foul fluid from its rear is so revolting that it can make people feel queasy up to a mile and a quarter away.

name: Skuntank
description: It attacks by spraying a repugnant fluid from its tail, but the stench dulls after a few squirts.

name: Bronzor
description: Ancient people believed that the pattern on BRONZOR’s back contained a mysterious power.

name: Bronzong
description: Ancient people believed that petitioning BRONZONG for rain was the way to make crops grow.

name: Bonsly
description: In order to adjust the level of fluids in its body, it exudes water from its eyes. This makes it appear to be crying.

name: Mime-jr
description: In an attempt to confuse its enemy, it mimics the enemy’s movements. Then it wastes no time in making itself scarce!

name: Happiny
description: It carefully carries a round, white rock that it thinks is an egg. It’s bothered by how curly its hair looks.

name: Chatot
description: It mimics the cries of other Pokémon to trick them into thinking it’s one of them. This way they won’t attack it.

name: Spiritomb
description: It was formed by uniting 108 spirits. It has been bound to the Odd Keystone to keep it from doing any mischief.

name: Gible
description: It nests in horizontal holes warmed by geothermal heat. Foes who get too close can expect to be pounced on and bitten.

name: Gabite
description: As it digs to expand its nest, it habitually digs up gems that it then hoards in its nest.

name: Garchomp
description: Its body is covered in fine scales that reduce drag, enabling it to fly at high speeds.

name: Munchlax
description: It conceals food under the long fur on its body. It carts around this food stash and swallows it without chewing.

name: Riolu
description: They communicate with one another using their auras. They are able to run all through the night.

name: Lucario
description: It’s said that no foe can remain invisible to LUCARIO, since it can detect auras. Even foes it could not otherwise see.

name: Hippopotas
description: It shrouds itself in sand to ward off germs. It travels easily through the sands of the desert.

name: Hippowdon
description: It brandishes its gaping mouth in a display of fearsome strength. It raises vast quantities of sand while attacking.

name: Skorupi
description: It burrows under the sand to lie in wait for prey. Its tail claws can inject its prey with a savage poison.

name: Drapion
description: It attacks people and Pokémon that cross the desert. This has only furthered its bad reputation.

name: Croagunk
description: Fluid squeezed from its finger, albeit poisonous, is a significant ingredient in remedies for lower back pain.

name: Toxicroak
description: Swaying and dodging the attacks of its foes, it weaves its flexible body in close, then lunges out with its poisonous claws.

name: Carnivine
description: It walks around on its tentacles in search of a tree branch where it can dangle down and ambush prey.

name: Finneon
description: Swimming and fluttering its two tail fins, it looks like a BEAUTIFLY. At night, the patterns on its tail fins softly shine.

name: Lumineon
description: LUMINEON swimming in the darkness of the deep sea look like stars shining in the night sky.

name: Mantyke
description: When it swims close to the surface of the ocean, people aboard ships are able to observe the pattern on its back.

name: Snover
description: During cold seasons, it migrates to the mountain’s lower reaches. It returns to the snow-covered summit in the spring.

name: Abomasnow
description: It lives a quiet life on mountains that are perpetually covered in snow. It hides itself by whipping up blizzards.

name: Weavile
description: It lives in snowy regions. It carves patterns in trees with its claws as a signal to others.

name: Magnezone
description: Exposure to a special magnetic field changed MAGNETON’s molecular structure, turning it into MAGNEZONE.

name: Lickilicky
description: It has space in its throat to store saliva. It can also roll up its tongue and store it in the same spot.

name: Rhyperior
description: From holes in its palms, it fires out GEODUDE. Its carapace  can withstand volcanic eruptions.

name: Tangrowth
description: Its vines grow so profusely that, in the warm season, you can’t even see its eyes.

name: Electivire
description: As its electric charge amplifies, blue sparks begin to crackle between its horns.

name: Magmortar
description: It blasts fireballs of over 3,600 degrees Fahrenheit out of its arms. Its breath also sears and sizzles.

name: Togekiss
description: As everyone knows, it visits peaceful regions, bringing them gifts of kindness and sweet blessings.

name: Yanmega
description: The beat of its wings is so powerful that it accidentally dislodges full-grown trees when it takes off in flight.

name: Leafeon
description: When you see LEAFEON asleep in a patch of sunshine, you’ll know it is using photosynthesis to produce clean air.

name: Glaceon
description: It causes small ice crystals to form by lowering the temperature of the surrounding atmosphere.

name: Gliscor
description: Its flight is soundless. It uses its lengthy tail to carry off its prey... Then its elongated fangs do the rest.

name: Mamoswine
description: It flourished worldwide during the ice age but its population declined when the masses of ice began to dwindle.

name: Porygon-z
description: Its programming was modified to enable it to travel through alien dimensions. Seems there might have been an error...

name: Gallade
description: Because it can sense what its foe is thinking, its attacks burst out first, fast, and fierce.

name: Probopass
description: It controls three units called Mini-Noses using magnetic force. With them, it can attack the foe from three directions.

name: Dusknoir
description: This feared Pokémon is said to travel to worlds unknown. Some even believe that it takes lost spirits along with it.

name: Froslass
description: Legends in snowy regions say that a woman who was lost on an icy mountain was reborn as FROSLASS

name: Rotom
description: Research continues on this Pokémon, which could be the power source of a unique motor.

name: Uxie
description: According to some sources, this Pokémon provided people with the intelligence necessary to solve various problems.

name: Mesprit
description: This Pokémon is said to have endowed the human heart with emotions, such as sorrow and joy.

name: Azelf
description: This Pokémon is said to have endowed humans with the determination needed to face any of life’s difficulties.

name: Dialga
description: This Pokémon completely controls the flow of time. It uses its power to travel at will through the past and future.

name: Palkia
description: Its total control over the boundaries of space enable it to transport itself to faraway places or even other dimensions.

name: Heatran
description: Boiling blood, like magma, circulates through its body. It makes its dwelling place in volcanic caves.

name: Regigigas
description: It is believed to have shaped REGIROCK, REGICE, and REGISTEEL out of clay, ice, and magma.

name: Giratina
description: This Pokémon is said to live in a world on the reverse side of ours, where common knowledge is distorted and strange.

name: Cresselia
description: Those who sleep holding CRESSELIA’s feather are assured of joyful dreams. It is said to represent the crescent moon.

name: Phione
description: When the water warms, they inflate the flotation sac on their heads and drift languidly on the sea in packs.

name: Manaphy
description: It starts its life with a wondrous power that permits it to bond with any kind of Pokémon.

name: Darkrai
description: It chases people and Pokémon from its territory by causing them to experience deep, nightmarish slumbers.

name: Shaymin
description: The blooming of Gracidea flowers confers the power of flight upon it. Feelings  of gratitude are the message it delivers.

name: Arceus
description: According to the legends of Sinnoh, this Pokémon emerged from an egg and shaped all there is in this world.

name: Victini
description: This Pokémon brings victory. It is said that Trainers with Victini always win, regardless of the type of encounter.

name: Snivy
description: It is very intelligent and calm. Being exposed to lots of sunlight makes its movements swifter.

name: Servine
description: It moves along the ground as if sliding. Its swift movements befuddle its foes, and it then attacks with a vine whip.

name: Serperior
description: It can stop its opponents’ movements with just a glare. It takes in solar energy and boosts it internally.

name: Tepig
description: It can deftly dodge its foe’s attacks while shooting fireballs from its nose. It roasts berries before it eats them.

name: Pignite
description: When its internal fire flares up, its movements grow sharper and faster. When in trouble, it emits smoke.

name: Emboar
description: It can throw a fire punch by setting its fists on fire with its fiery chin. It cares deeply about its friends.

name: Oshawott
description: It fights using the scalchop on its stomach. In response to an attack, it retaliates immediately by slashing.

name: Dewott
description: Strict training is how it learns its flowing double-scalchop technique.

name: Samurott
description: One swing of the sword incorporated in its armor can fell an opponent. A simple glare from one of them quiets everybody.

name: Patrat
description: Using food stored in cheek pouches, they can keep watch for days. They use their tails to communicate with others.

name: Watchog
description: When they see an enemy, their tails stand high, and they spit the seeds of berries stored in their cheek pouches.

name: Lillipup
description: It faces strong opponents with great courage. But, when at a disadvantage in a fight, this intelligent Pokémon flees.

name: Herdier
description: It has black, cape-like fur that is very hard and decreases the amount of damage it receives.

name: Stoutland
description: It rescues people stranded by blizzards in the mountains. Its shaggy fur shields it from the cold.

name: Purrloin
description: They steal from people for fun, but their victims can’t help but forgive them. Their deceptively cute act is perfect.

name: Liepard
description: These Pokémon vanish and appear unexpectedly. Many Trainers are drawn to their beautiful form and fur.

name: Pansage
description: This Pokémon dwells deep in the forest. Eating a leaf from its head whisks weariness away as if by magic.

name: Simisage
description: Ill tempered, it fights by swinging its barbed tail around wildly. The leaf growing on its head is very bitter.

name: Pansear
description: When it is angered, the temperature of its head tuft reaches 600° F. It uses its tuft to roast berries.

name: Simisear
description: It loves sweets because they become energy for the fire burning inside its body.

name: Panpour
description: The water stored inside the tuft on its head is full of nutrients. Plants that receive its water grow large.

name: Simipour
description: The tuft on its head holds water. When the level runs low, it replenishes the tuft by siphoning up water with its tail.

name: Munna
description: Munna always float in the air. People whose dreams are eaten by them forget what the dreams had been about.

name: Musharna
description: The mist emanating from their foreheads is packed with the dreams of people and Pokémon.

name: Pidove
description: Each follows its Trainer’s orders as best it can, but they sometimes fail to understand complicated commands.

name: Tranquill
description: It can return to its Trainer’s location regardless of the distance separating them.

name: Unfezant
description: Males swing their head plumage to threaten opponents. The females’ flying abilities surpass those of the males.

name: Blitzle
description: Its mane shines when it discharges electricity. They use their flashing manes to communicate with one another.

name: Zebstrika
description: They have lightning-like movements. When Zebstrika run at full speed, the sound of thunder reverberates.

name: Roggenrola
description: Its ear is hexagonal in shape. Compressed underground, its body is as hard as steel.

name: Boldore
description: When it overflows with power, the orange crystal on its body glows. It looks for underground water in caves.

name: Gigalith
description: Compressing the energy from its internal core lets it fire off an attack capable of blowing away a mountain.

name: Woobat
description: Its habitat is dark forests and caves. It emits ultrasonic waves from its nose to learn about its surroundings.

name: Swoobat
description: It emits sound waves of various frequencies from its nose, including some powerful enough to destroy rocks.

name: Drilbur
description: It can dig through the ground at a speed of 30 mph. It could give a car running aboveground a good race.

name: Excadrill
description: It can help in tunnel construction. Its drill has evolved into steel strong enough to bore through iron plates.

name: Audino
description: It touches others with the feelers on its ears, using the sound of their heartbeats to tell how they are feeling.

name: Timburr
description: It fights by swinging a piece of lumber around. It is close to evolving when it can handle the lumber without difficulty.

name: Gurdurr
description: This Pokémon is so muscular and strongly built that even a group of wrestlers could not make it budge an inch.

name: Conkeldurr
description: It is thought that Conkeldurr taught humans how to make concrete more than 2,000 years ago.

name: Tympole
description: They warn others of danger by vibrating their cheeks to create a high-pitched sound.

name: Palpitoad
description: When they vibrate the bumps on their heads, they can make waves in water or earthquake-like vibrations on land.

name: Seismitoad
description: They shoot paralyzing liquid from their head bumps. They use vibration to hurt their opponents.

name: Throh
description: When it tightens its belt, it becomes stronger. Wild Throh use vines to weave their own belts.

name: Sawk
description: The sound of Sawk punching boulders and trees can be heard all the way from the mountains where they train.

name: Sewaddle
description: Leavanny dress it in clothes they made for it when it hatched. It hides its head in its hood while it is sleeping.

name: Swadloon
description: Forests where Swadloon live have superb foliage because the nutrients they make from fallen leaves nourish the plant life.

name: Leavanny
description: Upon finding a small Pokémon, it weaves clothing for it from leaves, using the cutters on its arms and sticky silk.

name: Venipede
description: Its bite injects a potent poison, enough to paralyze large bird Pokémon that try to prey on it.

name: Whirlipede
description: Protected by a hard shell, it spins its body like a wheel and crashes furiously into its enemies.

name: Scolipede
description: With quick movements, it chases down its foes, attacking relentlessly with its horns until it prevails.

name: Cottonee
description: When attacked, it escapes by shooting cotton from its body. The cotton serves as a decoy to distract the attacker.

name: Whimsicott
description: Like the wind, it can slip through any gap, no matter how small. It leaves balls of white fluff behind.

name: Petilil
description: The leaves on its head are very bitter. Eating one of these leaves is known to refresh a tired body.

name: Lilligant
description: Even veteran Trainers face a challenge in getting its beautiful flower to bloom. This Pokémon is popular with celebrities.

name: Basculin
description: Red and blue Basculin get along so poorly, they’ll start fighting instantly. These Pokémon are very hostile.

name: Sandile
description: They live buried in the sands of the desert. The sun-warmed sands prevent their body temperature from dropping.

name: Krokorok
description: They live in groups of a few individuals. Protective membranes shield their eyes from sandstorms.

name: Krookodile
description: They never allow prey to escape. Their jaws are so powerful, they can crush the body of an automobile.

name: Darumaka
description: When its internal fire is burning, it cannot calm down and it runs around. When the fire diminishes, it falls asleep.

name: Darmanitan
description: Its internal fire burns at 2,500° F, making enough power that it can destroy a dump truck with one punch.

name: Maractus
description: It uses an up-tempo song and dance to drive away the bird Pokémon that prey on its flower seeds.

name: Dwebble
description: This Pokémon can easily melt holes in hard rocks with a liquid secreted from its mouth.

name: Crustle
description: Competing for territory, Crustle fight viciously. The one whose boulder is broken is the loser of the battle.

name: Scraggy
description: Its skin has a rubbery elasticity, so it can reduce damage by defensively pulling its skin up to its neck.

name: Scrafty
description: Groups of them beat up anything that enters their territory. Each can spit acidic liquid from its mouth.

name: Sigilyph
description: They never vary the route they fly, because their memories of guarding an ancient city remain steadfast.

name: Yamask
description: Each of them carries a mask that used to be its face when it was human. Sometimes they look at it and cry.

name: Cofagrigus
description: It has been said that they swallow those who get too close and turn them into mummies. They like to eat gold nuggets.

name: Tirtouga
description: Restored from a fossil, this Pokémon can dive to depths beyond half a mile.

name: Carracosta
description: They can live both in the ocean and on land. A slap from one of them is enough to open a hole in the bottom of a tanker.

name: Archen
description: Said to be an ancestor of bird Pokémon, they were unable to fly and moved about by hopping from one branch to another.

name: Archeops
description: They are intelligent and will cooperate to catch prey. From the ground, they use a running start to take flight.

name: Trubbish
description: Inhaling the gas they belch will make you sleep for a week. They prefer unsanitary places.

name: Garbodor
description: It clenches opponents with its left arm and finishes them off with foul-smelling poison gas belched from its mouth.

name: Zorua
description: It changes into the forms of others to surprise them. Apparently, it often transforms into a silent child.

name: Zoroark
description: Bonds between these Pokémon are very strong. It protects the safety of its pack by tricking its opponents.

name: Minccino
description: They greet one another by rubbing each other with their tails, which are always kept well groomed and clean.

name: Cinccino
description: Their white fur is coated in a special oil that makes it easy for them to deflect attacks.

name: Gothita
description: Their ribbonlike feelers increase their psychic power. They are always staring at something.

name: Gothorita
description: They use hypnosis to control people and Pokémon. Tales of Gothorita leading people astray are told in every corner.

name: Gothitelle
description: Starry skies thousands of light-years away are visible in the space distorted by their intense psychic power.

name: Solosis
description: They drive away attackers by unleashing psychic power. They can use telepathy to talk with others.

name: Duosion
description: Since they have two divided brains, at times they suddenly try to take two different actions at once.

name: Reuniclus
description: When Reuniclus shake hands, a network forms between their brains, increasing their psychic power.

name: Ducklett
description: These bird Pokémon are excellent divers. They swim around in the water eating their favorite food--peat moss.

name: Swanna
description: Swanna start to dance at dusk. The one dancing in the middle is the leader of the flock.

name: Vanillite
description: The temperature of their breath is -58° F. They create snow crystals and make snow fall in the areas around them.

name: Vanillish
description: Snowy mountains are this Pokémon’s habitat. During an ancient ice age, they moved to southern areas.

name: Vanilluxe
description: Swallowing large amounts of water, they make snow clouds inside their bodies and attack their foes with violent blizzards.

name: Deerling
description: The color and scent of their fur changes to match the mountain grass. When they sense hostility, they hide in the grass.

name: Sawsbuck
description: They migrate according to the seasons. People can tell the season by looking at Sawsbuck’s horns.

name: Emolga
description: The energy made in its cheeks’ electric pouches is stored inside its membrane and released while it is gliding.

name: Karrablast
description: These mysterious Pokémon evolve when they receive electrical stimulation while they are in the same place as Shelmet.

name: Escavalier
description: They fly around at high speed, striking with their pointed spears. Even when in trouble, they face opponents bravely.

name: Foongus
description: It lures people in with its Poké Ball pattern, then releases poison spores. Why it resembles a Poké Ball is unknown.

name: Amoonguss
description: It lures prey close by dancing and waving its arm caps, which resemble Poké Balls, in a swaying motion.

name: Frillish
description: With its thin, veil-like arms wrapped around the body of its opponent, it sinks to the ocean floor.

name: Jellicent
description: The fate of the ships and crew that wander into Jellicent’s habitat: all sunken, all lost, all vanished.

name: Alomomola
description: The special membrane enveloping Alomomola has the ability to heal wounds.

name: Joltik
description: Joltik that live in cities have learned a technique for sucking electricity from the outlets in houses.

name: Galvantula
description: When attacked, they create an electric barrier by spitting out many electrically charged threads.

name: Ferroseed
description: When threatened, it attacks by shooting a barrage of spikes, which gives it a chance to escape by rolling away.

name: Ferrothorn
description: It fights by swinging around its three spiky feelers. A hit from these steel spikes can reduce a boulder to rubble.

name: Klink
description: The two minigears that mesh together are predetermined. Each will rebound from other minigears without meshing.

name: Klang
description: By changing the direction in which it rotates, it communicates its feelings to others. When angry, it rotates faster.

name: Klinklang
description: Its red core functions as an energy tank. It fires the charged energy through its spikes into an area.

name: Tynamo
description: While one alone doesn’t have much power, a chain of many Tynamo can be as powerful as lightning.

name: Eelektrik
description: They coil around foes and shock them with electricity-generating organs that seem simply to be circular patterns.

name: Eelektross
description: They crawl out of the ocean using their arms. They will attack prey on shore and immediately drag it into the ocean.

name: Elgyem
description: It uses its strong psychic power to squeeze its opponent’s brain, causing unendurable headaches.

name: Beheeyem
description: It can manipulate an opponent’s memory. Apparently, it communicates by flashing its three different-colored fingers.

name: Litwick
description: Litwick shines a light that absorbs the life energy of people and Pokémon, which becomes the fuel that it burns.

name: Lampent
description: This ominous Pokémon is feared. Through cities it wanders, searching for the spirits of the fallen.

name: Chandelure
description: It absorbs a spirit, which it then burns. By waving the flames on its arms, it puts its foes into a hypnotic trance.

name: Axew
description: They use their tusks to crush the berries they eat. Repeated regrowth makes their tusks strong and sharp.

name: Fraxure
description: Since a broken tusk will not grow back, they diligently sharpen their tusks on river rocks after they’ve been fighting.

name: Haxorus
description: They are kind but can be relentless when defending territory. They challenge foes with tusks that can cut steel.

name: Cubchoo
description: When it is not feeling well, its mucus gets watery and the power of its Ice-type moves decreases.

name: Beartic
description: It can make its breath freeze at will. Very able in the water, it swims around in northern seas and catches prey.

name: Cryogonal
description: When its body temperature goes up, it turns into steam and vanishes. When its temperature lowers, it returns to ice.

name: Shelmet
description: When attacked, it defends itself by closing the lid of its shell. It can spit a sticky, poisonous liquid.

name: Accelgor
description: When its body dries out, it weakens. So, to prevent dehydration, it wraps itself in many layers of thin membrane.

name: Stunfisk
description: Its skin is very hard, so it is unhurt even if stepped on by sumo wrestlers. It smiles when transmitting electricity.

name: Mienfoo
description: In fights, they dominate with onslaughts of flowing, continuous attacks. With their sharp claws, they cut enemies.

name: Mienshao
description: It wields the fur on its arms like a whip. Its arm attacks come with such rapidity that they cannot even be seen.

name: Druddigon
description: It warms its body by absorbing sunlight with its wings. When its body temperature falls, it can no longer move.

name: Golett
description: The energy that burns inside it enables it to move, but no one has yet been able to identify this energy.

name: Golurk
